text: Holly Woodlawn (Haroldo Santiago Franceschi Rodriguez Danhakl; October 26, 1946 - December 6, 2015) was a transgender Puerto Rican actress and Warhol superstar. She was known for her roles in Trash (1970) and Women in Revolt (1972). Woodlawn died in Los Angeles, California from brain cancer and liver cancer at the age of 69. ==References== Category:1946 births Category:2015 deaths Category:Cancer deaths in Los Angeles Category:Deaths from brain cancer Category:Deaths from liver cancer Category:Puerto Rican movie actors Category:Transgender women
